        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. There was no data available for the production volume of 2-methyl-2-butanol. This is a placeholder value thats reflect the real-world production of a different amyl alcohol (1-pentanol, 2-methylbutanol) for Western Europe in 1988. The Western Europe production volume was scaled to reflect the world production considering the nominal GDP of Europe in 1988, equal to 4'574'521'460'013 US$ and in the World, equal to 19'394'022'898'347 US$. This has no negative effect on the results of the ecoinvent database. 
References:
Papa, A.J. (2000). Amyl Alcohols. In Kirk-Othmer Encyclopedia of Chemical Technology, (Ed.). https://doi.org/10.1002/0471238961.0113251216011601.a01
&lt;https://api.worldbank.org/v2/en/indicator/NY.GDP.MKTP.CD?downloadformat=excel&gt; 
</productionVolumeComment>
